Description: Model the health, education, and economic costs of directly
    transmitted respiratory virus pandemics, under different scenarios of
    prior vaccine investment, policy interventions, and public behavioural
    change, using the 'DAEDALUS' integrated health-economics model adapted
    from Haw et al.  (2022) <doi.org/10.1038/s43588-022-00233-0>.
